BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:&#8220\;Sky Dance&#8221\; &#038\; Twilight Hike at Beanblossom Bot
 toms
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T190000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T203000
UID:b67c2b62bb4b84adf1c63ff9d8deda52@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join guest hike leader and naturalist Cathy Meyer for an eveni
 ng of exploration along the boardwalk trails at Beanblossom Bottoms. As sp
 ring approaches in the wetlands\, a flurry of activity begins\, including 
 migration\, courtship\, and rising waters. The chorus of amphibians during
  this twilight hike will be the backdrop as we search the sky for the wood
 cock’s famous mating ritual\, the “sky dance.”
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2023/03/sky-dance-twilight-hike-at-beanb
 lossom-bottoms-2/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:April Fools&#8217\; Day Weed Wrangle
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T130000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T150000
UID:8c3ac4282cb07ddca6e3fcd882bf492f@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Volunteers are invited to help Sycamore preserve native biodiv
 ersity\, gain hands-on experience in land stewardship\, and help control i
 nvasive plants on our preserves!  Weed Wrangle events are fun and educati
 onal opportunities to learn how to identify and control the invasive plant
 s that are negatively impacting our preserves and other green spaces in ou
 r community. This event will be located at one of our non-public preserve
 s in Monroe County\, details and directions will be emailed after registra
 tion.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2023/03/april-fools-day-weed-wrangle/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
