BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Conservation Field Day
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T140000
UID:d94682f6ac3a415e72bb421f9fe920e0@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Curious about how conservation gets put into practice? Join th
 e Brown County Soil and Water Conservation District\, Dan McGuckin of Habi
 tat Solutions\, and Sycamore staff for an up-close look at the conservatio
 n practices Sycamore uses to improve soil and water quality and wildlife h
 abitat. We&#8217\;ll meet a the bottomland trail for discussion\, then hik
 e up the upland train to the bluffs overlooking Beanblossom Creek.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2019/03/conservation-field-day/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Eagle Slough Natural Area Birding Hike
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T070000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T090000
UID:7e2dec789282e0b42ac04dfe2ad4fb44@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join the Ohio Valley Birding Festival for an early morning bir
 ding walk through Sycamore&#8217\;s 127-acre property in Evansville\, IN. 
 Expect to see a variety of warblers\, migratory songbirds\, and late shore
 birds\, including Wood Ducks\, Winter Wrens\, vireos\, thrushes\, tanagers
 \, etc. Bring binoculars if you have them. Meet at the Eagle Slough entra
 nce on Waterworks Rd\, just north of Ellis Park. More information is at o
 hiovalleybirdingfestival.org.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2019/03/0419-eagle-slough/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Patoka River NWR Birding Hike
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260412T070000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260412T100000
UID:f05c53a85a24eb6ae90cde6830287333@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join the Evansville Audubon Society for a birding walk through
  Boyd Woods at the Patoka River National Wildlife Refuge\, where Sycamore 
 protects 1\,200 acres at Columbia Mine Preserve. We&#8217\;ll search for w
 arblers and other migratory songbirds\, continuing the hike past Snakey Po
 int Marsh for possible views of waterfowl and marsh birds\, and ending at 
 a little-visited portion of Columbia Mine Preserve to look for grassland s
 parrows.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2019/03/0419-patoka-birding-hike/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sycamore Branches: Hike &#038\; Brew
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T130000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T160000
UID:b840403c278ed75901af04570e84f39b@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join our young adults (and young at heart) group for a fun hik
 e at this beautiful\, secluded preserve\, followed by drinks and good conv
 ersation at the café at Lucky’s Market. Free admission\; drinks are on 
 you. All ages are welcome!
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2019/03/0419-branches-hike/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Brown County Hike
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T100000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T130000
UID:1b41cfd5e9ee6a0572f0527b156436c3@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Hike leader Anne Bornhorst\, ambassador for Women Who Hike\, s
 ays the terrain and seclusion make Downey Hill one of her favorite places 
 to hike. Anne says &#8220\;Sometimes you may be the only one there are Dow
 ney Hill to enjoy the peacefulness of the creeks and the sounds of the bir
 ds.&#8221\; On this hike\, you&#8217\;ll be challenged by the ruggedness o
 f the south and north loop trails\, cross creeks\, wander past a pond\, an
 d spot a few old wells that remind us of the past lives this area has expe
 rienced.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2019/02/brown-county-hike/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
